<paragraph id="8B84368D731AAB484385FA6CFBC0F987" blockId="111.[151,1436,1431,1565]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis id="B94FEA9F731AAB484385FA6CFE85FA4E" bold="true" box="[199,273,1468,1493]" pageId="111" pageNumber="112">Notes.</emphasis>
A widespread western species but poorly documented in the Eastern United States. The occurrence in Michigan was confirmed from a male specimen deposited at the UMMZ. The biology of this ground-nesting species has been studied in Alberta (
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B7C731AAB48416CF9D4FD2FF986" author="Hobbs" box="[558,699,1540,1565]" firstAuthor="Hobbs" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" pagination="625 - 631" refId="ref90334" refString="Hobbs, G. A. (1956) Ecology of the leaf-cutter bee Megachile perihirta Ckll. (Hymenoptera: Megachilidae) in relation to production of alfalfa seed. The Canadian Entomologist, 88, 625 - 631. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / ent 88625 - 11" type="journal article" year="1956">Hobbs 1956</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B7C731AAB484185F9D4FC38F986" author="Hobbs &amp; Lilly" box="[711,940,1540,1565]" firstAuthor="Hobbs" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" pagination="453 - 462" refId="ref90432" refString="Hobbs, G. A. &amp; Lilly, C. E. (1954) Ecology of species of Megachile Latreille in the mixed prairie region of southern Alberta with special reference to pollination of alfalfa. Ecology, 35, 453 - 462. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 1931035" type="journal article" year="1954">Hobbs &amp; Lilly 1954</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAA4B7C731AAB4840FAF9D4FBD3F987" author="Sladen" box="[952,1095,1540,1565]" firstAuthor="Sladen" pageId="111" pageNumber="112" pagination="301 - 304" refId="ref102841" refString="Sladen, F. W. L. (1918) Pollination of alfalfa by bees of the genus Megachile. Table of Canadian species of the latimanus group. The Canadian Entomologist, 50, 301 - 304. https: // doi. org / 10.4039 / ent 50301 - 9" type="journal article" year="1918">Sladen 1918</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
